Run the main code on any python compiler.
Download required libraries.
Once you run the code, a GUi will pop up which will be your user interface.
In GUI, enter IP address of esp32_cam, u get upon running the basic example code of esp32_cam module on arduino ide by connecting the module.
Copy that IP adress and paste it in the GUI where it is asked.
Then paste deployment id or url as asked, after creating a google script in your specific google drive to download and saving of image as your requirements.
Then press Connect button in GUI to connect the esp32_cam module.
Then live streaming is enabled and camera is connected successfully.
To capture the image select the take photo option to capture the image, and automatically image will saved in google drive.
If u want to click or capture images automatically, enter the time in seconds u want each photo to be captured. 
